  "text": "Best orr was 25%, demonstrated in 8 patients. Of those 8 patients, 6 had asps; an orr of 50.4% was demonstrated in the 11 evaluable patients with asps. A separate paper by Lewin et al. [CITATION_1] also described the responses seen in asps patients. In that paper, mismatch repair deficiency signatures were cited as a putative reason for the high response rates seen in patients with asps treated with icis. In Canada, a basket study using a similar strategy (axitinib-pembrolizumab) has recently started randomizing lms patients, among others, to durvalumab with or without cediranib or olaparib (see NCT03851614 at https://ClinicalTrials.gov/).",
